HEADWORD: Tinean
<hw>Tin"e*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any species of Tinea, or of the family <fam>Tineidae</fam>, which
includes numerous small moths, many of which are injurious to woolen and
fur goods and to cultivated plants. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tined</ent>⟦br⟧
